### Package

filament/filament

### Package Version

v5.6.7

### Laravel Version

v13.15.0

### Livewire Version

v4.3.1

### PHP Version

v8.4.22

### Problem description

When `\Filament\Navigation\NavigationGroup::fromEnum` is checking if the Enum implements `Collapsible`, the order of operations appears wrong within the `if` statement.

https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/5.x/packages/panels/src/Navigation/NavigationGroup.php#L143-L146

The NavigationGroup::collapsed() method also sets collapsible to whatever value collapsed is.  But because the `fromEnum` method calls `collapsible` first, then `collapsed`, you can never set a navigation group to be collapsible, but NOT collapsed initially.

I believe the order of the calls in `fromEnum` should be flipped, so that `collapsed` is called first, and then `collapsible`.

### Expected behavior

Here's an enum example that I would expect to result in a Navigation group that is collapsible, but not initially collapsed.  But what actually happens it that the group is not collapsible at all.

### Steps to reproduce

Example Enum:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Enums;

use Filament\Support\Contracts\Collapsible;
use Filament\Support\Contracts\HasLabel;
use Illuminate\Contracts\Support\Htmlable;

enum AppNavigationGroups implements HasLabel, Collapsible
{
    case GROUP;

    public function getLabel(): Htmlable|string|null
    {
        return match ($this) {
            self::GROUP => 'Group',
        };
    }

    public function isCollapsible(): bool
    {
        return match ($this) {
            default => true,
        };
    }

    public function isCollapsed(): bool
    {
        return match ($this) {
            default => false,
        };
    }
}
```

Within a Panel, use it:

```php
$panel->navigationGroups(\App\Enums\AppNavigationGroups::class)
```

